Governors elected on the platform of the All Progressives Congress are currently at the National Secretariat of the party in Abuja in a bid to continue the discussion with the National Chairman, Adams Oshiomhole, and National Working Committee over the rift between him and governor of Edo State, Godwin Obaseki. The meeting was conveyed in a desperate attempt to douse tensions in the party ahead of the Edo and Ondo governorship primaries. SaharaReporters gathered that the meeting was a continuation of the one held with national leader of the party, Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu, in Lagos on Sunday night. Among the governor that were seen at the Secretariat include the chairman of Progressives Governors Forum and Governor of Kebbi State, Atiku Bagudu, Ondo State governor, Rotimi Akeredolu, Lagos State governor, Babajide Sanwo-Olu, Plateau State governor, Simon Lalong, Kano State governor, Abdullahi Ganduje, and Kwara State governor, Abulramam Abdulrazak, were all sighted at the APC National Secretariat. 